headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 45 points and 11 assists to lead the Milwaukee Bucks to a 141-135 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard has 45 points and 11 assists to lead the Bucks past the Pistons, 141-135

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 33 points to extend his franchise-record run of 30 or more to 20 games and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Charlotte Hornets 97-89 on Saturday night for their fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid scores 33 points, 76ers beat Hornets 97-89 for 5th straight victory

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama returned after sitting out a game to score 24 points and grab eight rebounds, leading the San Antonio Spurs to a 131-127 victory over the Washington Wizards on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama returns to score 24 points, lead Spurs over Wizards, 131-127

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell had 18 points and eight assists to lead a balanced attack as the Cleveland Cavaliers extended the NBA's longest current win streak to seven games with a 116-95 win over the Atlanta Hawks on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavs extend NBA's longest win streak to seven with balanced 116-95 win over Hawks

events.name: Toronto Raptors at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle felt things were out of place when he saw Immanuel Quickley bringing the ball up the court after Toronto won the opening tip.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle's triple-double leads Knicks over Raptors as Barrett, Quickley return to MSG after trade

headlines.description: — The Chicago Bulls know what they have to do to come away with a win when Zach LaVine is not in the lineup.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dosunmu, DeRozan lead way as Bulls pound Grizzlies, 125-96

headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun scored a career-high 37 points and had a game-high 14 rebounds to lead the Houston Rockets to a 127-126 overtime win over the Utah Jazz on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sengun scores a career-high 37, Rockets outlast Jazz in OT 127-126

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 11 of his 33 points in the fourth quarter and the Oklahoma City Thunder rallied to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 102-97 on Saturday night in a matchup of the top teams in the Western Conference standings.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scores 33 points, Thunder beat Timberwolves 102-97 in West showdown
